markets.title: Will the United States average less than **25,000 new COVID-19 cases** per day by April 1?
markets.subtitle: <25k
markets.rules_primary: If the seven-day moving average of new COVID-19 cases for the United States according to the CDC is below 25,000 for a single day between Issuance and April 01, 2022, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: Note that this Contract may close and expire early. It will expire the first 10:00 AM following the CDC reporting the event has occured, the first 10:00 AM following data being released for April 01, 2022, or 10:00 AM on April 08, 2022.
